#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:9
#: 2eb110b8f961430baae62565467e69a2
msgid ""
"Software that is too complicated to use, is often unused. Because we want as"
" many people as possible to benefit from its unique security properties, the"
" usability and user experience of Qubes OS is an utmost priority!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:11
#: c8471192f3164208a221daa1e70b3ecc
msgid ""
"We ask anyone developing for Qubes OS to please read through this guide to "
"better understand the user experience we strive to achieve. We also ask them"
" to review [our style guide](/doc/style-guide/) for other design related "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:15
#: 9f7360ecefc640498d7875616a7bdcd4
msgid "Easy To Use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:17
#: 21f8612101b64cbc90cc50872880549c
msgid ""
"An ideal user experience is friendly, and it beckons a new user to explore "
"the interface. In this process, they can naturally discover how to use the "
"software. Below are some guidelines that will help you design a user "
"interface that accomplishes this goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:23
#: 7975137908dd46faaee8c2a3a9d9279c
msgid "Require extensive configuration before a user can *begin* doing things"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:24
#: 7f6211cb8c8f43f983e171fe7e842175
msgid ""
"Make it possible to break provided features or actions in unrecoverable ways"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:25
#: e3a8d789f8a945b4aff605c7e0990cf6
msgid "Perform actions which compromise security and data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:26
#: 609763dc52d840dea4e1fbde412ed060
msgid "Overwhelm the user with too much information and cognitive load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:28
#: e5e5f02f90bd4591b37b855470e09124
msgid ""
"Perhaps the most common cause of mistakes is complexity. If there is a "
"configuration setting that will significantly affect the user's experience, "
"choose a safe and smart default then tuck this setting in an `Advanced "
"Settings` panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:34
#: 8f030f824e544b4caee45f49a43595b5
msgid "Make it easy to discover features and available actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:35
#: f574f3e510f84479ae55123d2e6924d8
msgid "Provide some understanding of what discovered features do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:36
#: 30ae2798d585423f823ef66ca184056a
msgid "Offer the ability to easily undo mistakes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:37
#: 501902a97613439ab67da73328e339d6
msgid "Choose intelligent defaults for settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:39
#: d872b9ade7104ef89ac9e5fa1ca51b66
msgid ""
"In making software easy to use, it is crucial to be mindful of [cognitive "
"load](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognitive_load) which dictates that "
"*\"humans are generally able to hold only seven +/-  two units of "
"information in short-term memory.\"* Making sure your interfaces don't pass "
"this short-term memory limit is perhaps the most important factor in helping"
" a user feel comfortable instead of overwhelmed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:43
#: 6b11be3576194fc4a7b8ea32d9fad27b
msgid "Easy to Understand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:45
#: cd5b2c184d8b425e972224b3a6b1f845
msgid ""
"There will always be the need to communicate things to users. In these "
"cases, an interface should aim to make this information easy to understand. "
"The following are simple guides to help achieve this - none of these are "
"absolute maxims!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:51
#: 5f916cce435443deb3681f922f4d919a
msgid ""
"Acronyms are compact and make good names for command line tools. They do not"
" make graphical user interfaces more intuitive for non-technical users. "
"Until one learns an acronym's meaning, it is gibberish. Avoid acronyms in "
"your interfaces whenever possible!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:53
#: 6be5ad030f064c078d7dc46df149103b
msgid "`DVM` - Disposable Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:54
#: bd258197e6054ead8a408d71fdb35610
msgid "`GUID` - Global Unique Identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:55
#: 699f66c77c0d4e0db922f9deda662cf8
msgid "`PID` - Process Identification Number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:56
#: c2b6ae935c1b43bd8ef0f4d22f5b73dd
msgid "`NetVM` - Networking Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:58
#: 672604be2567465f9c9c232d2f8d4e1f
msgid ""
"Despite this rule, some acronyms like `USB` are widely used and understood "
"due to being in common use for over a decade. It is good to use these "
"acronyms when the full words like `Universal Serial Bus` are more likely to "
"confuse users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:64
#: b218a839cb1a4d3a993343f76a2b002c
msgid ""
"Use the minimum amount of words needed to be descriptive, but also "
"informative. Go with common words that are as widely understood. Sometimes, "
"inventing a word such as `Qube` to describe a `virtual machine` makes the "
"life of the user much easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:66
#: d69b510dfa4a470c84eee297272739c0
msgid "Use `Disposable Qube` instead of `DVM` or `Disposable Virtual Machine`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:67
#: 356bfebc48a241e397db2db7afe3bbc0
msgid "Use `interface` instead of `GUI` or `Graphical User Interface`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:68
#: 1e3ebc62929742a1a95f200c4040d617
msgid ""
"Use `application number` instead of `PID` or `Process Identification Number`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:69
#: db16032aa0c540dca8520322c9bbef05
msgid "Use `Networking` or `Networking Qube` instead of `NetVM` given context"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:77
#: 2c31fa05e4cb4e6c9532c49dea8b870a
msgid ""
"Technical words are usually more accurate, but they often *only* make sense "
"to technical users and are confusing and unhelpful to non-technical users. "
"Examples of technical words that might show up in Qubes OS are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:79
#: 51aa505684c64cd58e8ba08f5a34accd
msgid "`root.img`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:80
#: 5cfbc2b2e78c4ff5bc23cb8a83626451
msgid "`savefile`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:81
#: 4646342c2f09411e92437ba49d989d34
msgid "`qrexec-daemon`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:83
#: 2f50496720c04646ab89c62c74419181
msgid ""
"These are all terms that have at some point showed up in users' notification"
" messages. Each term is very specific, but requires the user to understand "
"virtualization to interpret."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:89
#: 831f92b243cb46d08ad1302fb82e230b
msgid ""
"Large amounts of the global population have been using computers for one or "
"two decades and have formed some mental models of how things work. "
"Leveraging these mental models are a huge gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:91
#: 819b98a9d07c4d4cb49bee6530180504
msgid ""
"Use `disk space` instead of `root.img`, since while not quite accurate, it "
"makes contextual sense"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:92
#: b129be6f95e04ad08eda3ef195f5a91b
msgid ""
"Use `saving` instead of `savefile` as the former is the action trying to be "
"completed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:93
#: 2ff4fa74028b4883b30d7fa444a4c113
msgid ""
"Use `Qubes` instead of `qrexec-daemon` as it gives better context on what is"
" happening"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:95
#: cb686fed4a274f9eb5e2efc46ef653b9
msgid ""
"These words are more abstract and user relevant- they help a user understand"
" what is happening based on already known concepts (disk space) or start to "
"form a mental model of something new (Qubes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:103
#: 9c0f532ba24f42ca8a09971ac2d72142
msgid ""
"It is easy to start abbreviating (or making acronyms) of long terms like "
"`Disposable Virtual Machine` depending on where the term shows up in an "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:105
#: 86ecdee4834c4f1ea8318779bbd4af41
msgid "`DVM`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:106
#: b089bbd52ee840198624989f1594f28c
msgid "`DispVM`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:107
#: c1d4ad2e26974180b974b8d1e84b9684
msgid "`DisposableVM`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:109
#: 7e0d61dc8a6f41f58432d297e19dce23
msgid ""
"This variation in terms can cause new users to question or second guess what"
" the three different variations mean, which can lead to inaction or "
"mistakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:115
#: 7b8ac901deaf493dba08b7b2b7043997
msgid ""
"Always strive to keep things consistent in the interfaces as well as "
"documentation and other materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:117
#: 4318f62324ba4e6aa688fa84bfd80d21
msgid "Use `Disposable Qube` at all times as it meets other criteria as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:119
#: a7e8ba7f8c6f43fa81f0ccd91bcf8db5
msgid ""
"By using the same term throughout an interface, a user can create a mental "
"model and relationship with that term allowing them to feel empowered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.md:127
#: 586c64d64bc441678fd8ef430cdbe8b0
msgid ""
"It is easy to add words like `Domain` before items in a list or menu in an "
